1. Login with root user
2. Create a user with name "classic"
3. Set password for user "classic", password should be "redhat"
4. Read first 5 lines of /etc/passwd file with a single command
5. Read last 4 lines of /etc/passwd file with a single command
6. Could all lines of /etc/passwd file
7. Login with user student on the terminal
8. From "student" user switch to the "classic" user and provide the password when asked.
